SA Paralympic archer Shaun Anderson; and Danelle Wentzel, who is a regular in the South African team; Wian Roux, who is going to represent South Africa at the Youth Olympic Games; and World Masters Championship silver medal winner Beyers de Klerk volunteered to help. Tuks’ Gerda Roux identified at least two girls who might pursue the sport. “If just one of these archers can represent South Africa at a World Championships, we would have succeeded in what we set out to achieve.” - African News Agency (ANA)